@jeffnorris8848 Do you really think it's only about oil? 

Your debt exploded when you started the Iraq war, for around 7 trillion USD in total. Now, when you're around 38 trillion in debt, you wanna start another one? And we are talking about Iran, not Iraq. People are saying it will be 3 or more times more expensive (because of geographical, military capabilities, and geopolitical factors that Iran has), but even if we are charitable and say it's only double. You still don't have and for sure are not in a position to start a war with them.

And guess who will pay that mountain of debt? Don't fool yourself, the government will not pay for you. It will be you! From more taxes and more tariffs.

