So that’s not an example or description of how bad the economy currently is. 
Compare the US economy to Iran for example or Maybe your country.

@bonar1211 The IMF projects U.S. real GDP growth of 2.6% in 2026, reflecting a resilient economy despite fiscal and trade challenges.
Growth Forecast
The International Monetary Fund (IMF) has raised its 2026 U.S. real GDP growth forecast to 2.6%, slightly above its January projection of 2.4%. This growth reflects continued strength in private sector productivity, particularly from AI-integrated business models and a robust services sector, as well as resilient consumer spending supported by a tight labor market.  Is this a BAD or GOOD economy??

